12. Memory Overhead
-------------------

Vector:

Stores only data.

List:

Stores:

data
prev pointer
next pointer

More memory per element.

Interview Q:
Why does list consume more memory than vector?

Answer:
Because every node stores two extra pointers in addition to the data.

-----------------------------------------

13. When to Use list?
---------------------

Use list when:

✓ Frequent insertions/deletions in middle
✓ Iterator stability is important

Avoid list when:

✗ Random access required
✗ Cache efficiency important
✗ Mostly sequential storage

